# UI Design Rules

Design language: **precision-minimalist B2B tool** (Linear/Notion direction). No gradients, no glass, no decorative flourishes.

## Surfaces

| Surface | Class |
|---|---|
| Page background | `bg-[#f5f6f8]` |
| Card / panel | `bg-white border border-gray-300` |
| Sidebar | `bg-[#111111]` (only dark surface in the app) |
| Sticky header | `bg-white border-b border-gray-200 shadow-sm sticky top-0 z-10` |

## Border Radius

- Entity cards (projects, runs): `rounded-2xl` — max allowed
- Data panels, table wrappers: `rounded-xl`
- Badges, pills, avatars: `rounded-full`
- Never use `rounded-3xl` or above

## Typography

```
Page title:      text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900
Section header:  text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900
Table headers:   text-xs font-semibold text-gray-600 uppercase tracking-wide
Body:            text-sm text-gray-700
Secondary/meta:  text-xs text-gray-500
IDs / indexes:   text-xs font-mono text-gray-500
```

## Status Badges (exact classes — do not deviate)

```tsx
// Pass
"bg-green-50 text-green-700 border border-green-200 rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-semibold"
// Fail
"bg-red-50 text-red-700 border border-red-200 ..."
// Warn / Retest
"bg-yellow-50 text-yellow-700 border border-yellow-200 ..."
// Pending / Skip
"bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 border border-gray-300 ..."
```

Status colors (green/amber/red) are reserved exclusively for pass/warn/fail. Never use them for decoration.

## HeroUI Defaults

```tsx
<Input variant="bordered" size="sm" />       // ALL inputs
<Select variant="bordered" size="sm" />      // ALL selects
<Textarea variant="bordered" size="sm" />    // ALL textareas
<Button size="sm" />                         // ALL buttons
<Button size="sm" color="primary" />         // Primary CTA only
<Modal placement="center" />                 // ALL modals
```

Custom `classNames` pattern for inputs:
```tsx
classNames={{
  label: 'text-gray-700 font-medium',
  inputWrapper: 'border-gray-300 hover:border-gray-400',
}}
```

Never override border-radius on HeroUI components.

## Icons

Library: `lucide-react` only. Size conventions:
- `size={11}` — fill icons in tight stat rows
- `size={14}` — avatar-adjacent, dropdown chevrons
- `size={16}` — standard inline icons
- `size={17}` — sidebar navigation
- `size={22}` — empty state illustrations

Nav icons: `strokeWidth={2.2}` active, `strokeWidth={1.8}` inactive.

## Layout

```
Page container:    max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-8
Card grid:         grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4
Data panel grid:   grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6
Table wrapper:     bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm
```

## Interactions

- Cards: `hover:border-gray-400 hover:shadow-md transition-all`
- Table rows: `hover:bg-blue-50/30 transition-colors`
- Elevation: `shadow-sm` static max, `shadow-md` hover max — never `shadow-lg+`

## Avatars

`boring-avatars` variant `"beam"` with palette `['#0A0310', '#49007E', '#FF005B', '#FF7D10', '#FFB238']`.
Fallback: Lucide `<User>` icon.

## Never

- Gradients, glassmorphism, `backdrop-blur`
- A second font family
- `shadow-lg` or above on static elements
- Status colors outside of badges / pass-rate
- Hardcoded HeroUI primary blue hex — use `color="primary"` prop
- Inline `style={{}}` for values with Tailwind equivalents (except dynamic widths)
